3. Variables and types of Variables in power apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Variables are mainly used to store and manage data temporarily while the app is running. 
ğŸ‘‰ This data can any type, such as numbers, strings, or booleans, depending on the situation.

ğŸ”¹ Types of Variables:
1ï¸âƒ£ Context Variables are Scoped only to the current screen.
ğŸ’› Syntax: UpdateContext({ VariableName: Value }) || Example: UpdateContext({ varName: "Manoj" })  

2ï¸âƒ£ Global variables are accessible throughout the entire app across all screens.
ğŸ’› Syntax: Set( VariableName, Value ) || Example: Set(varCountry, "India") 

Example:
ğŸ‘‰ In my project, I used a Global variable to store logged-in user role, a Context variable to open and close popups, 
    and a Collection to cache SharePoint list data for faster performance.
