7. Explain the concept of Delgations in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Delegation means pushing data processing to the data source instead of the app, so the app can handle large datasets efficiently.
ğŸ‘‰ This is crucial When working with large datasets â€” for example, SharePoint lists with thousands of records.
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps has a default limit of 500 records (Which can be increase upto max 2000 records).
ğŸ‘‰ but without delegation, only those limited records are retrieved, leading to incomplete data.
To slove this, 
ğŸ‘‰ I always use delegable functions like Filter, Sort, and StartsWith so the heavy lifting happens on the server, ensuring accurate and efficient data retrieval.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

